==English==
===Etymology===
Of American origin.  Derived from Classical Greek '''αυτός (autós)''', meaning "self" + English '''-ism'''

===Noun===
'''autism'''
# Abnormal self-absorption, first observed in childhood, characterised by lack of response to people and limited ability to communicate.

